{"id": "EUVD-2022-54679", "enisaUuid": "e0d2f7a9-32e6-3b46-a6b9-788abe0e743d", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nfs/ntfs3: validate BOOT sectors_per_clusters\n\nWhen the NTFS BOOT sectors_per_clusters field is > 0x80, it represents a\nshift value.  Make sure that the shift value is not too large before using\nit (NTFS max cluster size is 2MB).  Return -EVINVAL if it too large.\n\nThis prevents negative shift values and shift values that are larger than\nthe field size.\n\nPrevents this UBSAN error:\n\n UBSAN: shift-out-of-bounds in ../fs/ntfs3/super.c:673:16\n shift exponent -192 is negative", "datePublished": "2025-10-22T18:30:31", "dateUpdated": "2025-10-22T18:30:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/58cf68a1886d14ffdc5c892ce483a82156769e88", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4746c49b11b2403f5b5b07c6eac9e60663dcd9a3", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a2b6986316a2d106f6951e76db70fa4b2fde64a9", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a3b774342fa752a5290c0de36375289dfcf4a260", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-49553"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-49553"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.04, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "3067c0e8-8076-37bc-9da8-dcf880c3c1c0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "82cae269cfa953032fbb8980a7d554d60fb00b17 <4746c49b11b2403f5b5b07c6eac9e60663dcd9a3"}, {"id": "3eb2a65f-3be7-3f0e-908e-6e09faa8d666", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.15"}, {"id": "4ea2b552-1e16-3830-9f64-9d51e4e487c0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.15.45"}, {"id": "6fcdb763-629f-36c8-a1f0-c658ee5e1322", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.17.13"}, {"id": "75dc2674-fe62-3107-bd6c-d5ec9e0cbc7e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.19"}, {"id": "8132f304-c423-3946-ae89-c04405bfd151", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "82cae269cfa953032fbb8980a7d554d60fb00b17 <a3b774342fa752a5290c0de36